description: "The Human Race Part One: Radio Days." A pair of hostile aliens forces Wally to race Kwyzz, a strange childhood friend of Wally's that came through the radio from another world.
name: The Human Race part 1 of 3

volume.name: Green Lantern / Sentinel: Heart of Darkness

description: Impulse shaves all his hair off and uses a wig to put on while he's Bart. Bart is part of the court session case of the toxic waste dumpers. Impulse meets the Song of Justice.
name: Court dates
Eclipsed the Secret Origin of Umbra!

description: The focus is on Captain Marvel, Jr. as the nightmare that is Dr. Morpheus forces the young Marvel to face his greatest fears! Are they really tormenting our hero--or are they just deadly phantoms of his life coming to exact revenge through his subconscious?
name: CM3

description:
Events near an explosive climax in Part 3 of the 4-part ""War in the Sun."" Panzers forward! Starr springs his trap, Jesse takes his life in his hands, the Saint of Killers loses his sense of humor, and Tulip learns whether she can get by with just a pretty face--or if she'll need a heavy machine-gun too.

Jesse tells the Saint about his origin; Starr goes to war; the Army is outmatched.
name: Come And Get It (War in the Sun Part 3)

description: In "The City" part 1, four self-contained stories focusing on 1939 New York City begin. The Golden Age Sandman crosses the bridge to the Bronx to find out why protection-racket enforcers are disappearing on the job, but could get burned by the answer.
name: The City Act I of IV

description: The Shade and Matt O'Dare cut through Opal City's seedy underworld to protect the secrets of Matt's criminal past. To what lengths are they willing to go to keep his dark secrets?
name: Villain's Redemption

description:
In the self-contained "Another Cold Morning," Spider Jerusalem, outlaw journalist, walks with the Revivals--people who have come out from cryogenic freeze into a world they don't understand, clinging to life in a city that has forgotten them completely.

Spider discusses the Revivals, people who have been revived from cryogenic storage after long periods of time. Almost all Revivals are unable to deal with the modern world and are generally ignored by the public. Spider makes friends with one Revival, a photojournalist from the 20th century named Mary.
name: Another Cold Morning

description: A psychotic cop in league with Mr. Fear is stirring up trouble. This corrupt cop has targeted Foggy Nelsons sisterfor death! Daredevil must save an innocent life before time runs out.
name: So Little Time To Save the World

description: The Heroes require backup when rescuing a scientist from the clutches of Silver Sable and her Wild Pack. Enter Deadpool? Will this be a decision Luke Cage and Iron Fist come to regret?
name: Misalliances!

description: Its up to Scarlet Witch and Quicksilver to singlehandedly save New Attitlan! Maximus has mind-controlled his way to a plot of destruction. Will the Inhumans finally see through his jig? A rollicking adventure from Marvels most dynamic sibling duo!
name: ...Mists & Tempests...

description: The new super-duo of Grizzly and Gibbon is caught by the White Rabbit. So the bouncing Bag-Man arrives to save them last minute. Anna Watson suspects Peter betraying Mary Jane - because once Anna herself had an affair. And in the end MJ proudly presents the Prodigy!
name: Through the Looking Glass

description:
Blastaar creats a gap in the space-time-continuum, which links the Negative Zone and our good ol' universe 616. Spider-Man is the first hero to notice that gap and has to stop Blastaars conquer. While SHOC keeps the gap open, Spider-Man runs into a civil war in the Negative Zone. He gains a strange black costume from the dying rebel's leader and can now create the identity of Dusk. By using its hidden powers and his own intelligence Spidey then knocks out Blastaar and returns to home.

Well, now he had to fulfil the mission to find the real Dusk, but that was ignored in following issues.
name: It Started On Yancy Street... Again!

description: It is an end for most of the heroes in this time line. The crews of the Enterprise A, the Excelsior and the Bounty are surrounded on the ground and in orbit of Planet Algol Two. There is escape for any of them as they fight to the death to bring the young Mia Colt home in hopes of correcting the timeline.
name: Now And Then

description: On her continuing journey back home, the U.S.S. Voyager comes under attack! Forced to crash land on a planet covered with water, Voyager must now deal with flood waters and a rapidly sinking ship!
name: Part One

description:
The Thunderbolts are transported to Kosmos!

After the Avengers stop Zemo from his plan of world domination, the Thunderbolts are teleported by a desperate race to their planet, but are soon imprisoned due to a crime that Erik Josten committed in his days of being Power Man. The prince of the planet meet with the Thunderbolts and state he is on their side after the Thunderbolts escape. They are soon imprisoned again, but Moonstone uses her phasing ability to find the planet's king's vizier and discuss an unknown diabolical plan.
name: In the courts of Kosmos!
If This Age Be Golden

description: Gambit is haunted in his dreams by the X-Men and Mister Sinister!
name: Once an X-Man/Guiding Light

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
The day before the now infamous school play.

Francine dreams of the perfect prom date. She is brought down to earth when a volley ball smacks her right in the face. It puts her on the benches until the end of the game. Katchoo see's Francine with a ruddy cheek a points at who might have done it. Francineisn'tsure so Kat pets a boll into the back of one of the girls. When one of the girls finds it funny Katchoo identifies her as the one who did it and throws a ball full in her face from close up. She runs around impishly. Katchoo gets detention for the rest of the day.

That night Katchoo turns up at Francine's window and finds out that Francine has an older brother Benjamin. they are obviously new friends as Katine tells Fran to call her Katchoo and explains the origin of the nickname.

Night of the play.
Backstage Freddie is bored and checking out the girls with a friend. His friend picks Francine, much to Freddie'sderision. Katchoo has now beensuspendedfor putting a cherry bomb into a boys locker. Francine gets her curtain call and we see the audiences faces and the round of the ripping material.

Francine is inconsolable at hime when theres a tap on her window again. Fran opens it and a badly beaten Katchoo slides inside.
name: Passion Cry
Remote Control

description: Woody is out for revenge, and Terrence Magnum, the man who has declared war on our heroes, is the target! Can Quantum keep Woody from going too far? Part one of the epic four part storyline Magnum Force!
name: Magnum Force Round 1: War
Breaking Point

description: The threat of the secret organization known as Locus continues to mount as the group continues its horrifying experiments--the ramifications of which will take a terrible toll on the unsuspecting Justice League members!
name: While You Were Out...
Climb Every Mountain to the HeadQuarters Without Fear!

description: Isadore Hibbert arrives to free her lover, jailed for his aristocratic connections. Fueled by romantic innocence and the support of two mysterious old shopkeepers, she makes a bid for her lover's freedom by first approaching the famed witch Catherine La Voisin.
name: Part One: Winter Into April

description: While seeking a break from their detective work, Sam and Twitch stumble on to a chaotic scene in a lounge that defies explanation. The bar patrons are fighting violently while appearing to be in a trance-like state. They then observe someone kidnapping one of the girls. Losing the suspect, they later find the girl with her throat ripped out. Meanwhile, as Spawn surveys the aftermath of the alley war, he is attacked by a vampire (Wolfram).
name: Apparitions
Xena: Warrior Princess vs Callisto Conclusion

description:
Cerne, a Millennium Giant, is headed towards Thierna Na Oge, and nothing Aquaman or any of his friends do can stop it. It destroys the city, but Spought saves a little of the mystic power so they can rebuild.

Aquaman and Tempest are once again forced to defend all of Atlantis as one of the Milenium Giants marches through the ocean, Aquaman then orders the city evacuated again to use it as a weapon against their foe while Vulko tries to convince Koryak to run for High Council. Aquaman then tries to use his telepathy to ward the giant away only for it to become angry setting it's sights on the two heroes. Fortunately Superman Red arrives to save them. Aquaman and Tempest then split up with Tempest preventing a tsunami from wiping out an island resort as Aquaman heads to regroup with Superman. Aquaman then uses his telepathy to force the giant to release a group of whales he has captured

Aquaman then uses all the firepower of his city, combined with Superman's full energy out put which has no effect. Aquaman then calls in the next wave of the attack the entire telekenetic power of the Thierna Na Oge to attack the giant. While Triton continues his plot bartering his protection to the mother of Monsters in exchange for the mother of all monsters. Superman once again joins his power with the Theierna Na Oge while Aquaman continues attacking telepathically knocking him over. However he isn't hurt getting right back up and heading to Nuada's city to destroy the power supply with Spought inside, however he is saved by Aquaman with the entire city being completely destroyed with most of their mystical power gone.
name: They Might be Giants
Xena: Warrior Princess: The Orpheus Trilogy

volume.name: Xena: Warrior Princess: The Orpheus Trilogy

description:
Noting that Flash and GL are no longer a threat to him, Prometheus shoots them out of spite and walks away, leaving them for dead.

Batman quickly recovers and is able to remove the bullet from GL; Flashs speed suit absorbed the kinetic force of his bullet.

Prometheus then breaks into the trophy room, where Superman and Wonder Woman are escorting the one hundred members of the media to the Martian shuttle bays. The media personal seem to be close to panic as Prometheus explains that any minute now Steels hammer will come crashing through an exterior wall of the Watchtower, causing an explosive decompression, which will kill everyone in the tower, (unknown to him Plastic Man has already intercepted Steel) except Superman. So, to save all those lives, he wants Superman to kill himself live on television; only then will he allow all the civilians to escape.

CatwomanIt is then that the only unforeseen variable makes her move. Catwoman, formerly disguised as Cat Grant, went along to see if she could steal a few things from the Watchtower; decides that she doesnt want to see so many people die, and whips Prometheus in the crotch with her bullwhip. Steel appears and takes control of Prometheus technology.

Prometheus decides to chalk this one up to experience and explains to flash that he was lying about the bombs, then teleports back to the Ghost-Zone, where he finds a very angry Zaurel, who he is forced to quickly send back to the Watchtower.
name: Prometheus Unbound!

description: As "Up the Down Staircase" concludes, the Mark of the Beast is everywhere, and the clue to beating the Devil--and saving Dani's brothers from his latest scheme--hides in plain sight.
name: Up The Down Staircase, Part 4

description: Deadpool gets recruited to the ranks ofLandau, Luckman, and Lake a strange organization that seems to be focused on saving the universe. While in their trans-dimensional headquarters Deadpool accidentally releases an alien beast from it cage. Now, it's up to him to stop it.
name: New Year's Evolutions or How to Get Ahead in Business Without Really Trying

description:
continued from Nightwing #19, continued next in Azreal #40

Shortly after the quake, it appeared Wayne-owned buildings were the only ones left without major structural damage. Bruce Wayne had seen to it that all of his buildings were quake-proof up to 8.5. Wayne Manor and the Batcave were destroyed. With all the exits blocked, Batman strapped on scuba gear and promised Alfred he'd be back soon. Barbara Gordon rallied the police force; Bulloch found Commissioner Gordon. At 8:52, the first aftershock hit.
name: Lifelines - Cataclysm, Part 3

description: The Joker is up to it again and with Batman out of the picture that means that makes Gotham a whole lot more harder. And it's up to James Gordon the commissioner of the Gotham police department to stop the joker but can Gordon stop the Joker.
name: Duty: Part One of Two

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
After draining Wolverine's lifeforce, Sauron attacks the X-Men!

A day of relaxation at the pond on the grounds of Xaviers Mansion is interrupted by the arrival of Sauron, who has just absorbed s mutant energy. The X-Men fight back, but Sauron grabs Cannonball in midair, then drops onto electrical lines, temporarily stunning him. Iceman launches icicles at Sauron, who briefly recalls stowing away in one of Ka-Zars crates as the jungle lord was relocating from the to . Coming out of his reverie, Sauron shoots Storm, grazing her, then Maggott dislodges the villains pistol and has his slugs destroy it.

As Iceman re-engages his reptilian foe, Sauron hypnotizes him into attacking his own teammates, then encasing Jubilee and himself in ice. Next, Maggott leaps from a treetop onto Saurons back.

Meanwhile, in space, Deathbird continues to use her spacecrafts medical equipment to heal the injured Bishop, but he questions her statements that the rest of the X-Men had perished, and that he is paralyzed. Without warning, they are fired upon by a spherical spacecraft, and their disabled ship begins a freefall toward a nearby star.

Inside Xaviers Mansion, Rogue, hurt by the accusation of her teammates that she attacked , finds Joseph unconscious. Using CPR, she revives him as Marrow slyly accuses her of trying to absorb Josephs powers. She again runs out of the mansion.

On the grounds, the battle continues as Sauron hurls Maggott toward the ground. His slugs devour enough of the soil of soften the impact, which nonetheless stuns him, Storm and Cannonball. Jubilee breaks free of her ice prison, but Sauron knocks her cold and crows in triumph as the X-Men lie unconscious about him.

In , Scott Summers, recovering from recent injuries, tries to fine tune his control over the strength of his eyebeams. Jean Grey enters the room, shocking Scott when he sees his wife wearing her original green costume.

Outside Xaviers, comes to and groggily challenges Sauron, who shows signs of exhaustion. The villain is finally defeated when Jubilee also revives and sets off her mutant fireworks by Saurons ears, knocking him out.

Later, as Rogue recalls how she found unconscious, then indeed absorbed some of his power, she hires a taxi to . Her destination is the Agee Institute where Dr. Agee claims to have a cure for mutations.
name: Prehistory

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Weatherman retrieves Apollo and Midnighter and soon realize they are both on the same side. Weatherman asks the duo to gather the technological advancement in Nevada Garden and they do, without it being able to be traced back to Stormwatch.
name: A Finer World: Part 3

description:
After the blood-filled events of last issue, the S.A.S. go after Tommy through his friends and kidnap Sean Noonan. Can Tommy calm down enough to save his friend...or will yet another buddy's blood leave a stain on his conscience? "Who Dares Wins" Part 3.

A British SAS hit-squad, trying to gain revenge for old friends lost, are having quite a bad-go of it themselves. And the Gotham Mafia is getting angry at things themselves but between Tommy and the best England has to offer, they are just a distraction.
name: Who Dares Wins, Part 3

deck: Cassandra (of Greek legend) tries to help Supergirl and Superman-Red deal with the Millennium Giants.
description: While the reincarnation of Cassandra watches, Cerne approaches an island to destroy it. Supergirl is worried about Sylvia Danvers and almost helps the giant; Tie-in to the Millennium Giants cross-over.
name: Things Best Left Forgotten

description: Trapped on a narrow ledge with the ferocious Kingdok ahead of them, the Bones and the Rat Creatures are forced to edge their way to safety along a precarious cliff face. As they do so, they are attacked by a swarm of locusts. Fone Bone stumbles and falls onto a lower ledge. The locusts try to carry him away, but the medallion given to him by Gran'ma Ben falls from his backpack and scares the locusts away. As the locusts flee, Kingdok vanishes into thin air, having been an illusion generated by the locusts' magic. Thanks to the orphans, the Bones realize the locusts could manipulate Thorn or even the whole valley with illusions, as they press on down the mountainside.
name: Ghost Circles

description:
Kyle deals with life after Donna Troy, he doesn't get much time to mope however as Grayven the son of Darseid comes knocking!

The story starts with kyle thinking about Donna troy the woman who up and left him, we learn why she did, since her son and ex husband had been killed and we also learn she left kyle not because of anything else than she thought she was bad luck and to protect him. Now I can say personally I would feel just as kyle did, unwanted, unloved, abandoned and DUMPED! those emotions came out clearly. Allison gives him a talk about how she can be there for him and they make a connection...hell! they would probably have ended up in bed if not for grayven terrorizing the city so kyle goes off to fight hm. The fight pans out all across the city till kyle kicks his ass, grayven teleports away with kyle in tow and he ends u somewhere else and gets jumped by a local mob...simply for being a green lantern!
name: Loose Ends

description: Lord Fanny's past as a prostitute in Brazil collides with her deadly present when a murderous secret agent tracks her through London. Plus, the Invisibles' search for Jack Frost continues.
name: Only Lovers Left Alive
Slave of Heavens, Part 3: Near Life Experience

description: Mitch and Hooker have their long-awaited showdown as Hooker finally gets what he has wanted all along: a piece of Resurrection Man's power. In this case it's a power of cosmic proportions and the battle between the super-beings may be the final death of one of them.
name: Origin of Species Pt. 2: The Shadow of Death
Paths of Glory, Throne of Blood

description:
(continued from Shadow of the Bat 73 - continued next in Batman 553)
Dick learned of the earthquake from TV at work. He bolted, grabbed a boat and headed to his former home. He was taken aback by the sheer destruction in Gotham City. He began helping victims trapped under a collapsed highway as soon as he got ashore.
name: Shudder

description: FF teams up with Moleman, who is plagued by Terminus.
name: The Enemy Within

description: Magnum Force Part 2 of 4, "Peace." Magnum's enforcer, War Locke, has taken the team captive and the guys learn the true price of being a superhero.
name: Magnum Force Round 2: Peace

description:
Supermen Red and Blue, the JLA, Superboy, Supergirl, and the Teen Titans have joined with Steel in the battle against the Millennium Giants, and John Henry Irons may have a solution that can stop these mammoth beings. Unfortunately, the solution may be as devastating as the problem.

Gigantic beings are smashing their way all across Earth.
name: Among Giants

description: Doctor Tomorrow closes out the 70s in a POW camp! After five years of eating bugs, it's time to hang up the super-threads and make some dough! The Doctor hits Wall Street during the biggest rush since 1929. Knowledge of th future can make Doc rich, but can it save his soul?
name: Journey From Tomorrow

description:
Overview

MOM#7 No less than seven Golden Age features reproduced in sharp clarity, six of them new to this title!! Columbia's Skyman battles giant Axis-spawned insects in an untitled story from Big Shot #32, (from February of 1942) drawn by his co-creator Ogden Whitney. The origin of Hillman Publication's The Heap is recapped in the first episode of his series in Airboy Comics, originally appearing in Vol. 3, #9, October, 1946. The Phantom Lady ends up in "The Old Shell Game", from PL's Ajax/Farrel run- Phantom Lady #2, February/March of 1955. Rocketman and Rocketgirl combat a murder racket in an untitled story from Chesler's Punch #19, drawn by Ralph Mayo; Fox Features' The Eagle thwart G. I. bankrobbers in a story taken from the second issue of his own book, published in September of 1941, and illustrated by Pierce Rice and Arturo Cazeneuve. Also, Bulletman and Bulletgirl face "Annihilation In The Air", drawn by Bill (Torchy)Ward, from Fawcett's Master Comics #99 Bonus: an all new "retro" adventure of The Fighting Yank and Kid Quick, written and drawn by Bill Black. Thrill to the fun, laughs and excitement as they take on the notorious and beautiful lady bandit known as Chili Con Carnage. There's all this, and more; all of it featuring the finest printing quality available. You won't find material like this anywhere else. Color cover by Bill Black, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.
name: An evil genius...

description:
Overview
This is the final issue of Concrete's origin tale and a never-before-told chapter in that saga. Concrete manages to slip away from agent Stamberg's goons for a second time -- this time to tie up some loose ends from his former life -- but Concrete's so busy worrying about his past, he fails to recognize Stamberg's nefarious plans for his future!

Carson Napier has come a long way since he first set foot on the exotic world of Amtor, but he still can't manage to avoid the slings and arrows of outrageous fortune. But when things look most bleak, and your wise cracks are falling on deaf ears, the howl of a jungle lord from a faraway green planet can only signal one thing: more trouble!
name: The Loveking - Part 1 of 4

description: Dick agrees to recover an artifact from Ra's Al Ghul for some African monks in exchange for a winged costume. He returns to Gotham with his new Nightwing identity.
name: Book Five: You Can't Go Home Again

volume.name: The Batman Adventures: The Lost Years

description: The original Challengers mix it up with aliens, planet-destroying weapons, and cosmic gods.

Sent to do a babysitting job as punishment for messing up her job in South America, Chase finally gets to meet her boss, Director Bones. Then her boyfriend, sister, and old business partner from San Fransico drop by, since it is just an easy job watching the Teen Titans premiere their new action figures. Then Booster Gold shows up and things get a little tense. But not as tense as when the Clock King and his new gang show up to crash the party and make a name for themselves.
name: Weep For The Future

description: Wally has a cosmic race with an energy creature named Kwyzz, who came through the radio from another world and was Wally's childhood friend.
name: The Human Race Part 2 of 3

description:
Heart of Darkness is a three issue Green Lantern storyline. The story begins with Kyle discovering that Jade, his girlfriend at that time and daughter of Alan Scott is missing. He contacts Alan Scott and together come to the conclusion that the biggest suspect would be Brainwave, an old nemesis of Alan Scott. While they go confront Brainwave to try and figure out whatever happened to Jade, who has been locked up, his brainwave powers ignite showing both Alan and Kyle memories of past that taunts them. The vision stops after Osidian, the son of Alan Scott, intervenes with an intention to kill brain wave. Thats the end of the first issue.

Second issue starts with Osidian trying to kill Brainwave but is stopped from doing so by Kyle and Alan Scott. Alan also find that Osidian has somehow changed, although he cant pinpoint how, and explain Osidian that he is convinced Brainwave isnt behind this and that Osidian needs to explain why hes so aggressive. Osidian is angered by this, and in turn attacks both Kyle and Alan, after a brief battle they find themselves teleported to a different realm, the realm of Starheart. Starheart is revealed to be behind the disappearance of Jade and has someone convinced Osidian to act in his regards. Starheart explains he did so because he believe Jade and Osidian are his children, although the biological component came from Alan Scott, the powers came from the Starheart. Starheart also explains that he wants them (Jade and Osidian) to embrace their heritage (as children of Starheart) and accept full power. It is also revealed that the reason Alan Scott was teleported to this realm was because he has in him a portion of Starheart power which Starheart now wants back. The issue ends with Alan giving up his powers and turning back to an old man.

In the third issue, Kyle confronts the Starheart and is easily overwhelmed; its obvious that Starheart is much more powerful than Kyle. Starheart grabs Kyle and is about to crush him when Jade agree to accept what Starheart wants, to accept the power and be the Starheart. Starheart then gives Jade a fraction of his powers after accepting which Jade attacks Starheart himself. After a brief battle its clear that Jade doesnt have enough power to match Starheart and the only way to do so is to truly embrace her heritage as a child of the Starheart. Jenny does so, fight and defeats Starheart, restores her father (Alan Scott) to his powers, and exorcises the part of Osidian that Starheart was controlling. In doing so she has used up the power she had gained from Starheart and leaves with Kyle with everything restored as it was.

volume.name: Green Lantern / Sentinel: Heart of Darkness

description: Dr. Morlo is back, but this time, he's come seeking Max and Impulse's help! Though Morlo has lived his life as a villain, he wants to save his son and his grandson from death at the hands of a maniacal and embittered old hero known as the Glory Slasher.
name: Generations of Crime
Casualty The Secret Origin of Star Boy

description: "The Monster Society of Evil" part 1! Mister Mind! Sin! Mister Atom! Sarge Steel! Alone, each has threatened the Captains Marvel and the world! Together, they are the Monster Society of Evil. Mister Mind returns to begin exacting his revenge on the Marvels and all of humanity!
name: The Monster Society of Evil! Part One

description:
(continued from Arkham Asylum: Tales of Madness)
Robin rescued "Hardback" Bock. Together, they took down Quakemaster - Arnold Wesker's newest puppet. Nightwing saved Gordon and Mayor Grange while Batman continued helping survivors.
name: Cataclysm, Conclusion: Flattened

description: The Golden Age Sandman's paramour, Dian Belmont, journeys to the borough of Staten Island in search of a legendary author who has vanished without a trace.
name: The City Act II of IV

description: A "Times Past" story of the Golden Age Starman and the Demon! When a troop of Nazis arrives in 1940s Opal City performing occult rituals, will the Demon Etrigan fight them--or help them? And can Ted Knight come to terms with the Demon's hell-spawned powers?
name: 1944: Science and Sorcery

description:
In this self-contained issue, outlaw journalist Spider Jerusalem investigates the Reservations, an area where previous cultures are carefully maintained in stasis, and discovers a place where an entirely new culture is being developed around body modification. Plus: Spider tries to ask a woman out...

Spider goes on a tour of the Reservations, places dedicated to preserving old Earth cultures. In general, he is impressed. Also, Channon decides to leave to become a nun.
name: Wild in the Country

description:
Captain America, fighting with his trusty team of Avengers, plans to take down Hydra once and for all in this issue!

Captain America and Thor have a good talk about how Cap's life is repeating lately. And the new hero worship is getting weird.
name: Power and Glory, Part 1: Credibility Gap

description: Luke Cage plots an escape heist after the Heroes are kidnapped by Silver Sable and the Wild Pack. And they dont call her pack wild for nothing. This is Luke Cage at his best!
name: Misalliances! The Conclusion

description: Ka-Zar conntinues to lose control over the Savage Land as Shanna's power grows to a dangerous levels!
name: The Politics Of Evolution

description:
In this flashback issue Quicksilver engages in an old-fashioned duel with Black Knightall for the love of Crystal! A retrospective featuring Pietros history with his Inhuman wife. Which man, (if any), will Crystal choose? Her estranged, impatient husband, or Black Knight, the honored Avenger?

Flashback of when Quicksilver is reunited with his wife Crystal, his sister the Scarlet Witch and The Black Knight! Quicksilver challanges the Black Knight for the hand of the lovelt Crystal but she gets annoyed and decides to go back to the Inhumans with Luna.
name: I Love You, Good-Bye

description:
In the midst of his identity crisis, Spider-Man tries out his newest costumed identity, Hornet, among other costumes.

This comic has two covers in one (so you had one comic, two covers), one saying Sensational Spider-man 27, the other Hornet number 1. The comic also came in two editions, one with the Spider-man cover on top, and one with the new identity on top.
name: Inventing the Hornet!

description:
In the midst of his identity crisis, Spider-Man tries out his newest costumed identity known, Prodigy, among other costumes.

This comic has two covers in one (so you had one comic, two covers), one saying Spectacular Spider-man 257, the other Prodigy number 1. The comic also came in two editions, one with the Spider-man cover on top, and one with the new identity on top.
name: Prodigy

description:
In the midst of his identity crisis, Spider-Man tries out his newest costumed identity, Dusk. It doesn't take long for him to break it in as the Shocker looks to collect a bounty on Trapster.

This comic has two covers in one (so you had one comic, two covers), one saying Peter Parker Spider-man 91, the other Dusk number 1. The comic also came in two editions, one with the Spider-man cover on top, and one with the new identity on top.
name: Undercover

description:
Captain Christopher Pike, Phillip Boyce and Spock have infiltrated a Temazi temple in order to find Klingons who are also in disguise as Temazi people. The Temazi will kill any off worlders and so the team has to find the Klingons before the Klingons find some ancient technological weapons.

Meanwhile in orbit of the planet Robert April feels that Pike's crew is under par including the acting Captain Number One. He is obviously wrong but he is also correct as the crew seems to raising tensions around the new crewman Shane Samson in engineering.
name: Thanatos

description: Grand Theft Spaceship with Chekov and Sulu!
name: Trekkers

description: Danger from the depths! Continuing the all-new limited series starring the crew of the U.S.S. Voyager!
name: Part Two

description:
History: (What If? II#108) - After Carnage's alien symbiote attached itself to the Silver Surfer, Spider-Man was lucky just to dodge his attacks. As the Carnage Cosmic, the Surfer attacked until he was temporarily stopped by the arrival of the Avengers, as well as Justice and Firestar of the New Warriors. Thor quickly threw his hammer at the Carnage Cosmic, but the Carnage Cosmic wrapped the hammer in symbiotic webbing and transformed into a giant spike heading back to Thor's hand. Iron Man managed to use his repulsors to break the symbiotic webbing, returning to use of Thor's hammer. After Captain America kicked the creature, the Vision phased his hand through the Carnage Cosmic's chest and attempted to solidify. When he did so, the Carnage Cosmic altered his own molecules to generate intense feedback into the Vision. Before the Avengers could rally themselves, the Carnage Cosmic blasted them all to the ground and flew off to create for mayhem.

The Avengers returned to Avengers Mansion to tend to the Vision's injuries as the Carnage Cosmic went global, causing mayhem wherever he went. The Avengers discussed the events that led to the Silver Surfer being attached to the Carnage symbiote and how the symbiote had left Cletus Kasady to die. Spider-Man explained that if the symbiote had enough time to permenantly bond with the Surfer, that there might not be any other way to stop him aside from killing him. After altering the molecular structure of the Statue of Liberty, the Carnage Cosmic once again met with the Avengers. The Carnage Cosmic easily bested the Avengers once again until Firestar managed to harm the symbiote enough to allow the Silver Surfer control over his body. Realizing that there was only way to stop the Carnage symbiote, the Silver Surfer flew himself into the sun, destroying both himself and the symbiote.
name: What If the Avengers Battled the Carnage Cosmic?

description:
A Thirty Two page Celebration.

A break from the usual format this comic is an extended issue with several all new shorts and stories.

  1. Akikos Guide to Earth
  2. How to Draw Poog
  3. Poog's Tale
  4. A Nice Long walk
  5. Dr's Orders

name: A Frim Grip on Reality!

description: Magnum Force Part 3 of 4: It's THE FEAR ISSUE- the guys, lost, their weapons and powers having proved useless against a relentless foe, are faced for the first time with the sobering reality of their imminent death (at the hands of War Locke). They become paralyzed by a crushing wave of fear in the final moments of their lives, confronting the true nature of heroism and friendship.
name: Magnum Force Round 3: Fear

description: Even for a dazzling, leggy Las Vegas showgirl, Nevada is exceptional. Her dancing partner and closest friend is an ostrich named Bolero. Her past is a mystery. And her life is about to take a turn for the weird, as a series of bizarre murders sets her on a collision course with a stalker ex-boyfriend, a drunken mystic, a would-be Godfather, and cosmic destiny.
name: Another Damn Suck-Egg Corpse

description: Fear and terror spread as the Brotherhood of Evil unleashes macabre plans, bringing the recently formed Justice League to its knees. The JLA's only hope may well rest with the bizarre team known as the Doom Patrol!
name: A League Divided
Young Heroes in: Oh My God! He's Dead!

description: In revolution-torn Paris, with the air literally smelling of blood, Isadore Hibbert leads her comrades Maude and Miro to La Grande Prison. As she nears the goal of the mission to which she has devoted her life, Isadore may have to choose between freeing her lover and freeing herself.
name: Part Two: April Into September

description:
The conclusion of the 4-part ""War in the Sun."" There are people who go too far. There are people who go way, way too far. There are people who go completely over the top. And then there's Starr.

Starr authorizes the last extreme measure against The Saint; Jesse sacrifices himself for his friends.
name: The Shatterer of Worlds (War in the Sun Part 4)

description: Bootsy steps between Spawn and Wolfram, the vampire, to keep them from destroying each other. When Wolfram mentions a nest of vampires in the area, Spawn goes to investigate just as the police arrive and take Bootsy in for questioning. At the police station, Bootsy passes a cryptic message to Sam and Twitch. Elsewhere in an abandoned warehouse, a child is being tortured. Spawn breaks in, kills the abusers and releases the child who reveals an emblem blazoned across his belly.
name: Bloodless
